extends ../partials/slide.pug

block content
    
  h1 Koala decline means economic decline

  p
    | According to the 
    +link('NSW Government','https://www.environment.nsw.gov.au/topics/animals-and-plants/native-animals/native-animal-facts/koala#:~:text=Koalas%20benefit%20the%20Australian%20economy,year%20to%20tourism%20in%20Australia.')
    | , koalas create over 9,000 jobs and contribute $1.1–2.5B to the state's economy each year. So while the State’s three-year, $44.7M Koala Strategy is significant, annually it is (at most) just 1.35% of the revenue koalas provide.
    
  p When the world looks at Australia, it looks for koalas — and seeing one in the wild is an experience only we can offer.


  .relative.mt-16.w-full.text-center.text-white.font-medium.bg-green-300.rounded.uppercase.text-sm.tracking-wide(style="height: 5rem; line-height: 5rem") Koala contribution to NSW economy
    .absolute.h-full.rounded-l.bg-green-100.left-0.top-0(style="width: 1.35%")
      .absolute.left-0.whitespace-no-wrap.text-green-100.text-sm.leading-none(style="top: 6.25rem;")
        span NSW Investment in Koala Strategy
        svg.absolute.left-0.fill-current(xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="8" viewBox="0 0 3.06 4.03" style="top: -14px;")
          polygon(points="3.06 1.53 2.06 0.53 1.53 0 1 0.53 0 1.53 0.53 2.06 1.16 1.44 1.16 4.03 1.91 4.03 1.91 1.44 2.53 2.06 3.06 1.53")

  #obama.absolute.hidden.opacity-0.inset-x-0.bottom-0.slide-up-full
    .mx-auto(style="transform: translateY(2.5rem) rotate(-30deg); max-width: 120px;")
      +picture(imgpath, "obama", ["jpg"], "President Obama with a koala")
